        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare metabolic myopathy presenting during childhood and characterized clinically by growth failure severe muscle weakness and moderate sensorineural deafness and biochemically by metabolic acidosis elevated serum pyruvate concentration hyperalaninemia and hyperalaninuria. There have been no further descriptions in the literature since 1973."
